  "release_notes": "Default stick-figure character flipped from 'plain' to 'top_hat'. The character preference is stored per-machine in chairside_ready_alert_config.json, so Fieldcrest's Mac install (which had been switched to top_hat via the picker) and the new Windows install (with no character key in its config) were rendering different figures — Mac had the hat, Windows didn't. Changing the default in load_animation_character() / set_character() so any config missing the animation_character key now resolves to top_hat. Existing configs with an explicit animation_character value are not touched — users who picked a different character through the picker keep their pick.",
